CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1950, pg. 2, reads: "Murder Suspect Questioned - Capt. Peter J. Weicht, head of the Homicide Division of the Police Department, questioned John Duffy, Tuesday, suspect in murder of Kelley Johnson of Wylie Avenue, in a speakeasy last Saturday night. Duffy allegedly stabbed Johnson to death after the latter became involved in a fight with Arthur Walls, a friend of Duffy's. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of John Duffy wearing plaid trousers and shoes with holes, posed in police captain's office
